## Edge Cases Handled

| Case | Solution |
|------|----------|
| User context missing | Default to OFF (safe) |
| Flag definition corrupted | Kill switch triggers safe mode |
| Network down for >5min | Cache staled, features off |
| Backend lag in flag update | Frontend updates first, backend catches up via verification |
| Millions of flags | Lazy-load flag definitions by name, not all at once |
| Time-based rollouts | Include `timestamp` in context, evaluate deterministically |
| A/B tests | Use different `rolloutSeed` per experiment |

This design trades occasional latency (one 30s sync interval) for complete consistency and instant kill-switch capability.
